/**
 * An optional value: either present or absent.
 *
 * Models a value that may be missing without resorting to a sentinel or an error — `some(x)` holds a
 * present value and `none` marks its absence. It is also the result of a `Coerce` conversion: `some`
 * carries the converted value when the coercion exists, and `none` signals that it does not.
 */
type Option[A]

/**
 * The absent case of `Option`.
 */
def none[A]: Option[A]
